      </subsection>

      <subsection name="Examples" id="Examples">
        <p>Please take a look at the following examples to understand how the check works:</p>

        <p id="Example1-code">Example #1: Block comments.</p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example1.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example2-code">
          Example #2: Comment is placed at the end of the block and has previous statement.
        </p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example2.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example3-code">
          Example #3: Comment is used as a single-line border to separate groups of methods.
        </p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example3.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example4-code">Example #4: Comment has distributed previous statement.</p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example4.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example5-code">
          Example #5: Single line block comment is placed within an empty code block.
          Note, if comment is placed at the end of the empty code block, we have Checkstyle's
          limitations to clearly detect user intention of explanation target - above or below. The
          only case we can assume as a violation is when a single-line comment within the empty
          code block has indentation level that is lower than the indentation level of the closing
          right curly brace.
        </p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example5.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example6-code">Example #6: 'fallthrough' comments and similar.</p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example6.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example7-code">Example #7: Comment is placed within a distributed statement.</p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example7.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example8-code">
          Example #8: Comment is placed within an empty case block.
          Note, if comment is placed at the end of the empty case block, we have Checkstyle's
          limitations to clearly detect user intention of explanation target - above or below. The
          only case we can assume as a violation is when a single-line comment within the empty case
          block has indentation level that is lower than the indentation level of the next case
          token.
        </p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example8.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example9-code">
          Example #9: Single line block comment has previous and next statement.
        </p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example9.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
        <p id="Example10-code">
          Example #10: Comment within the block tries to describe the next code block.
        </p>
        <macro name="example">
          <param name="path"
                 value="resources/com/puppycrawl/tools/checkstyle/checks/indentation/commentsindentation/Example10.txt"/>
          <param name="type" value="code"/>
        </macro>
